Hi! Our team is considering using a Laser CAN for coral identification. Before we make the purchase, I was wondering what other teams expiriences were? Was it easy to set up? How tolerant is it? Would you reccomend the purchase?

Thanks!

I posted a little about our experience over in this thread a few months ago:

Announcing the LaserCAN from Grapple Robotics Electrical
I remember having similar issues during build season with GrappleHook this past year. It seemed rather temperamental as to when the software would detect/connect to the Rio (and subsequently any LaserCANs attached). I recall our “solution” was effectively connect/disconnect from the Rio half a dozen times until the connection decided to establish itself… (Not exactly helpful here, I know). I loved our LaserCANs, and once they were setup (CAN Id’s set) we didn’t have a single issue during a matc…

Tl;Dr: we had some initial setup issues (it sounds like grapple has been working to fix these issues for this season), but outside of that, we found them to be reliable throughout our season. We’ve already got a spot or two where they’ll be used on this year’s robot.

Extremely positive so far. They’re extremely precise, easy to tweak, and small so you can mount them wherever it’s needed. The configuration software is really well thought out, so it’s easy to get the data that you need.

This season has been rough (software issues prevented the tool from working, which is the only way to configure certain settings like the CAN ID), but this is fortunately resolved.
